title.undefined: Circular Economy Ontology Network (CEON) - Product Module

description.undefined: The Product module of CEON (Circular Economy Ontology Network).

title.value: Circular Economy Ontology Network (CEON) - Product Module

coversRequirements.value: In addition to requirements covered by imported ODPs, covers the following requirements from Onto-DESIDE D3.2: CE5-2, C1-4, C2-5, C5-3, C11-2, C12-1, C13-3, C13-4, C13-9, E1-4, E1-5, E1-15, E2-1, E3-2, E3-5, E4-1, E4-2, E4-8, E4-9, E6-7, T4-3, T4-5, T6-1, T8-3, T9-2.
In addition to requirements covered by imported ODPs, covers the following requirements from Onto-DESIDE D3.1: CVN-Resource-2, CVN-ResrouceType-4, C11-2, C12-1, C13-3, E2-1, T8-3.

comment.undefined: Represents that something is compliant with some standard or has a received a certain certification.
The location of supplier of a product or item.
Resource quality is derived based on assessments of resources considering the conditions and properties.
A constituent is a component of object.
The rules or restrictions made or maintained by authorities.
The generic relation representing the particpation of a resource in some relation. For example, it can be specialized to represent a reified version of an object or data property.
Represents the participation of objects in some situation.
A product composition is the composed information of a product in terms of a specific component, in which such a component is also a matter.
A digital object, e.g. a computer file, that is located on some server, hard drive, or on the web. Most often the digital object is the realization of some piece of information.
A batch of objects is a collection of physical objects that are of the same type, e.g. a set of items (product instances) adhering to the same product model.
A product composition is the composed information of a product in terms of a specific component, in which such a component is also a product.
The origin location of a physical object
The location where a physical object is assembled.

The relation involving the role of a certain actor with respect to a certain resource, e.g. an organisation or individual (actor) owning (role) a specific product (resource) at a specific point or period in time.

The relation involving the role of a certain actor with respect to a value network or a process in such a network, e.g. an organisation (actor) acting as the recycler (role) in a glass recycling value netowrk (network) at a specific point or period in time. Or an organisation (actor) acting as the dismantler (role) in a dismantling step of a building deconstruction process (process step) at a specific point or period in time.
RoHS (Restriction of Hazardous Substances in Electrical and Electronic Equipment) compliance is a compliance issuing that RoHS objectives are satisfied.
Product or service, or a combination thereof, that fulfils a need of an interested party.
A set of objects is a set of physical objects (items) that can be of different types, i.e. different kinds of items.

An item is a physical object put into a market for sale, i.e. corresponding to an individual of a product. The item can be a thing that grows naturally or produced through some chemical or manufacturing processes.
A product object composition is the composed information of a product object in terms of a specific component, in which such a component is also a product object.
Something that the actor is capable of doing, e.g. perfomring a certain role in a process, based on some properties, such as access to infrastructure, resources and know-how.
Information is an abstract concept that represents any kind of interpretations. For instance, information can be data generated by software systems or data used by people for communications.

Physical-based object designed for or utilized with a purpose. A product can be, for example: goods of any type; hardware (e.g. engine mechanical part, spare parts, consumables); electrical or electronic hardware devices or components (e.g. computers, communication equipment and sensors); processed materials (e.g. lubricant, cement).
A relation that represents a composing relation.
An infrastructure refers to facilities, services, or systems for participations to function.
The characteristics or attribuets of a resource.

A role that an actor can take in a specific context. Applies both to roles in the context of resources, such as owner, manufacturer, reseller etc. of that resource, as well as roles in relation to a circular value network, such as recycler, dismantler, transporter etc., in relation to a material flow.
The location where a physical object is manufactured.
A matter is a physical substance.
The production location of a physical object
Asset is sth that is valuable and useful to be used in activities, or owned by actors.
The status of a resource.
ISO compliance is a compliance issuing thay sth (e.g., organization's structure, business operations, practices or policies) follows a specific ISO standard.
REACH (Regulation on the registration, evaluation, authorisation and restriction of chemicals) compliance is a compliance issueing that the REACH regulation is satisfied.

Asset from which a solution is created or implemented. Depending on the context, reference to “resource” includes “raw material”, “feedstock”, “material” or “component”. Resource includes any energy type (e.g. the energy content or energy potential of materials). Note 4 to entry: Resources can be considered concerning both stocks and flows.
A physical object is a collection of matter.
An agent able to act in the context of a circular value network, e.g. an organisation, person.
The point in time when something took place or was valid.
Used to represent the country of assembly of a product or product object (item).
Relates some properties to the capability, such as the parameters of it, or the needed resources.
The end of a time interval.
Relates to the actor holding the capability.
